Well - I - I - I should imagine every night except - Friday we didn't because my mother never had any money by Friday and we always had - she used to wait for my fa
ther to come home with his money and she used to send me to the grocers for a - a large John West tin of salmon which was a shilling and a ha'penny I think. And we had - we had that for our tea - always on a Saturday - Friday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14883545 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2183528\charrsid6448569 Did you ever use any tinned meat?
